canonical:
  title: 諸葛殷知榷酒務
  author: 崔致遠
  language: lzh
  text: 牒奉處分榷酤之權起於漢代會計之利著在周經旣當預備闕懸難可不從改作將成重務固選良才前件官隱豹含章卧龍襲慶潔己則隋珠無類在公則庖刃有餘昨分孔僅之重司已成歷試今躡魯匡之良策何憚專勤無辭鄭驛之卑棲早致卓爐之餘利能資美祿必贍雄師所期百姓無譁非阻三軍告醉事須差攝舘驛巡官專知榷酒務
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 諸葛殷知榷酒務
  author: 崔致遠
  language: lzh
  text: 牒奉處分。榷酤之權。起於漢代會計之利。著在周經。旣當預備闕懸。難可不從改作。將成重務。固選良才。前件官。隱豹含章。卧龍襲慶。潔己則隋珠無類。在公則庖刃有餘。昨分孔僅之重司。已成歷試。今躡魯匡之良策。何憚專勤。無辭鄭驛之卑棲。早致卓爐之餘利。能資美祿。必贍雄師。所期百姓無譁。非阻三軍告醉。事須差攝舘驛巡官專知榷酒務。
korean:
  title: 제갈은 지 각주무
  author: 최치원
  language: kor
  text: 처분을 받들어 통첩한다. 술을 전매하는 권리는 한(漢)나라 때 생겼고, 회계(會計)의 이익은 주(周)나라 글에 나타나 있다. 이미 결원이 생긴 고을에는 마땅히 예비하여야 할 것이니, 그 자리에 사람을 새로 충당해야 한다. 그리하여 앞으로 무거운 책무를 이루려면, 진실로 훌륭한 인재를 뽑아야 하는 것이다. 전건의 제갈은 숨은 표범이 문채(文采)를 가지고, 엎드린 용이 상서를 지닌 것과 같아 몸을 깨끗이 하는 것은 수후(隋侯)의 구슬은 티가 없는 것과 같으며, 공무에 힘쓰는 것은 포정(疱丁)의 칼이 여유가 있는 것과 같다. 그 전에는 옛날 공근(孔僅)이 맡았던 그런 중책을 맡아서 경험을 많이 쌓았고, 이제는 옛날 노광(魯匡)의 양책(良策)을 좇고 있으니, 어찌 자리를 전담해서 하는 것을 꺼리리오. 정역(鄭驛)처럼 낮은 벼슬에 깃들이고 있으면서도 이를 사양하지 않고, 탁로(卓爐)가 일찍이 여유 있는 이익을 이룬 것처럼 해나갈 것이다. 뿐만 아니라 훌륭한 녹으로 반드시 많은 군사를 넉넉히 잘 먹일 것이다. 백성이 아무 원성이 없고 삼군(三軍)이 취(醉)하도록 기대하니 마땅히 관역 순관(館驛巡官)을 섭직하고, 각 주무를 전담하게 하라.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1090_010_0130&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: Appointment of Zhuge Yin as Superintendent of the Wine Monopoly
  author: Choi Chi-won
  language: eng
  text: |-
    By official proclamation, we hereby announce this appointment. The monopoly on wine sales arose in the Han dynasty, and the principles of fiscal management are recorded in the Zhou classics. Since vacant positions have emerged in the provinces, we must prepare replacements accordingly. To establish this important office, we must indeed select capable talent.

    This official, Zhuge Yin, is a hidden leopard bearing literary grace, a reclining dragon carrying auspicious virtue. In personal conduct, he is pure as the Pearl of Suihou—without flaw. In public service, he moves like Pao Ding's blade—with perfect economy of motion. Previously, he bore the heavy responsibilities that once fell to Kong Ji, gaining much experience through trial. Now he follows the wisdom of Lu Kuang—why should he hesitate to undertake this charge? Let him not shrink from this post, though it may seem humble as the station of Zheng Yi, yet he shall achieve profit as surely as Zhuo Lu once did. With generous provisions, he shall surely sustain the great army well. We anticipate that the people will voice no complaint, that the three armies shall lack no refreshment. Therefore, let the circuit inspector of the relay stations be assigned as superintendent with full charge of the wine monopoly.
  footnotes:
    - Kong Ji and Lu Kuang were legendary administrators of monopolies in ancient China, known for their fiscal acumen and integrity.
    - Pao Ding (庖丁) is the famous butcher from Zhuangzi whose blade never dulls because he cuts with perfect precision, never touching bone—here representing perfect efficiency.
    - The Pearl of Suihou is a legendary treasure symbolizing purity and perfection without blemish.
    - This appears to be an official appointment document promoting an administrator to oversee wine taxation, a major source of state revenue in medieval East Asia.
